<FIRST>u i AM-Israel-Lebanon     09-03 0210</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Israel-Lebanon,0216</SECOND>
<HEAD>Israel Bombs Guerrilla Base in South Lebanon</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Israeli warplanes destroyed a guerrilla base in
south Lebanon 21 miles north of the Israeli border Monday, the army
said.
   All planes returned safely from the early morning raid, a
military statement said.
   An army spokesman said the planes struck a guerrilla base in the
village of Majdal Balhis, about three miles east of Mashghara. The
spokesman, who is not identified under military regulations, would
not say which militia operated the base nor give the reason for the
raid.
   The air raid follows attacks Wednesday and Thursday in which
Katyusha rockets were fired at Israel's Galilee district from south
Lebanon. The attacks caused no injuries, but one rocket damaged a
house in Kiryat Shmona in the Galilee Panhandle.
   Israeli authorities blamed that rocket attack on the militant
Shiite Moslem militia Hezbollah, or Party of God.
   Also on Thursday, Israeli troops fought a battle with four
guerrillas just north of the border, and one member of the Shiite
militia Amal was killed. Israel suffered no casualties in the
firefight.
   The air attack was the the 10th time Israeli war planes have
struck in Lebanon this year. The last raid, on Aug. 27, was aimed at
a Hezbollah base.
</TEXT>
