<HEAD>26 Injured in Chain-Reaction Pileup on Autobahn</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MUNICH, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A chain-reaction pileup involving 115
vehicles on a major autobahn injured 26 people on Sunday,
authorities said.
   Police blamed the series of collisions on drivers traveling too
fast during a heavy rainstorm. Four of the victims were seriously
injured.
   The pileup occurred near Allershausen, 30 miles north of Munich,
creating a traffic jam 12 miles long on the autobahn linking
Nuremberg and Munich.
   Police said $445,000 in damage was done to vehicles involved.
