<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--PsychicsBan     09-03 0163</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Psychics Ban,0169</SECOND>
<HEAD>Old Law Against Psychics Halts Convention</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HUTCHINSON, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The psychics' convention here has been
canceled due to unforeseen circumstances.
   The clairvoyants canceled their get-together because an
almost-forgotten 1909 ordinance forbids psychics from practicing
their craft in this central Kansas city.
   Ian Bliss, a psychic from Colorado Springs, Colo., who organized
the fair, called the ordinance archaic and a violation of his civil
liberties.
   Another psychic, Judy Haynes Williams, who moved to the area
three years ago, complained that the ordinance kept her from
advertising her business. She said the city attorney's office told
her the ordinance would be enforced.
   The psychics' cancellation prompted city officials to say Friday
they would consider repealing the law.
   City Commissioner Ron Leslie said he wanted to know why city
fathers passed the ordinance in the first place.
   ``It's difficult for me to visualize that a bunch of people who
get together to talk about ESP represents a major problem,'' he said.
