on corruption and perjury charges.
   The trial was suspended in July when Blanco, 63, was allowed to
travel to Miami to accompany his wife, Asela Mera, hospitalized for
a broken ankle suffered during a fall in a stairwell.
   ``I've come to continue with the trial which began April 19 and
demonstrate my innocence,'' Blanco said after arriving.
