heart treatment and was sentenced in absentia to 20 years in prison
and fined $16.4 million.
   He returned to the Dominican Republic in November 1988 to appeal
the sentence and was immediately jailed. He was freed on bail July 5
to accompany his wife to Miami.
   Under Dominican law, the former president had the right to a new
trial upon returning to this Caribbean nation.
   The court has already heard testimony from 78 witnesses, and has
yet to hear testimony from Blanco and former Armed Forces Minister
Manuel Antonio Cuervo Gomez, who faces the same charges.
   Two businessmen convicted with Blanco in November, Leonel Almonte
and Juan Tomas Pena Valentin, are serving 20-year prison terms.
