a firecracker 23 minutes into the second half of the match at Rio's
Maracana stadium, when Brazil was ahead 1-0.
   The goalie, bleeding from an inch-long cut in his face, was taken
off the field by his teammates, who refused to return. Brazil, a
three-time world champion, was declared winner of the match.
   A Chilean official said the game would be protested to FIFA, the
international soccer association.
